com.vdisk.net.session

类 AbstractSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vdisk.net.session.AbstractSession
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Session
    直接已知子类:
    VDiskAuthSession

    public abstract class AbstractSession
extends Object
implements Session
    Keeps track of a logged in user and contains configuration options for the VDiskAPI. This is a base class to use for creating your own Sessions.

      • AbstractSession

        public AbstractSession(AppKeyPair appKeyPair,
               Session.AccessType type)
        Creates a new session with the given app key and secret, and access type. The session will not be linked because it has no access token pair.

      • AbstractSession

        public AbstractSession(AppKeyPair appKeyPair,
               Session.AccessType type,
               AccessToken accessTokenPair)
        Creates a new session with the given app key and secret, and access type. The session will be linked to the account corresponding to the given access token pair.

      • sign

        public void sign(HttpRequest request)
        Signs the request by using's OAuth's HTTP header authorization scheme and the PLAINTEXT signature method. As such, this should only be used over secure connections (i.e. HTTPS). Using this over regular HTTP connections is completely insecure.
        指定者:
        sign 在接口中 Session
        参数:
        request - an HttpRequest.
        另请参阅:
        Session.sign(HttpRequest)

      • getProxyInfo

        public Session.ProxyInfo getProxyInfo()
        Will be called every time a request is made to VDisk, in case the proxy changes between requests. Return null if you do not want to use a proxy, or a Session.ProxyInfo object with a host and optionally a port set.

        The default implementation always returns null.
        指定者:
        getProxyInfo 在接口中 Session

      • getHttpClient

        public HttpClient getHttpClient()
        Will be called every time a request is made to VDisk, in case you want to use a new client every time. However, it's highly recommended to create a client once and reuse it to take advantage of connection reuse.

        The default implementation does all of this and more, including using a connection pool and killing connections after a timeout to use less battery power on mobile devices. It's unlikely that you'll want to change this behavior.
        指定者:
        getHttpClient 在接口中 Session

        private String makeUserAgent()

      • setRequestTimeout

        public void setRequestTimeout(HttpUriRequest request)
        Will be called every time right before a request is sent to VDisk. It should set the socket and connection timeouts on the request if you want to override the default values. This is abstracted out to cope with signature changes in the Apache HttpClient libraries.

        The default implementation always sets a 30 second timeout.
        指定者:
        setRequestTimeout 在接口中 Session
